  "title": "Core Concepts of Foundations of Getting Started with Python",
  "lessonText": "In this section, we will explore the core concepts foundational to getting started with Python.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- **What is Python?** A high-level programming language known for its readability and simplicity.\n- **Why Learn Python?** It's versatile, widely used in various fields, and has a supportive community.\n- **Basic Syntax:** Python uses indentation to define code blocks, making it visually clear.\n- **Variables:** Containers for storing data values, defined using a name and an assignment operator.\n- **Data Types:** Common types include integers, floats, strings, and booleans.\n- **Control Structures:** Includes conditionals (if statements) and loops (for, while) to control the flow of your program.\n- **Functions:** Reusable blocks of code that perform a specific task, defined using the `def` keyword.\n- **Comments:** Use `#` for single-line comments to annotate your code without affecting execution."
  }
}
